import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import seaborn as sns
data =  pd.read_csv('D:\SAKETH and FUN\MY ENGINEERING\ENGINEERING 6TH SEM\DATA SC USING PY\ACADMICS\datsets\\literacy.csv')
lit=data.dropna(axis=0, how='any', thresh=None, subset=None, inplace=False)

print("EXTRACTING STATE WITH MAX LITERACY RATE:")
x=lit.max()
print(x)

print("EXTRACTING STATE WITH Min LITERACY RATE:")
y=lit.min()
print(y)

print("AVERAGE LITERACY RATE of YEARS")
print(lit.mean(axis=0))

print("AVG FOR ALL STATES")
avgw=lit.mean(axis=1)

states=lit.iloc[:,0]
print(pd.concat([avgw,states],axis=1))
x1=lit.iloc[:,3]
y1=lit.iloc[:,6]

plt.subplot(2,1,1)
plt.hexbin(x1,y1,gridsize=(10,10),cmap=plt.cm.BuGn_r)
plt.colorbar()
plt.xlabel("1991 literacy")
plt.ylabel("2001 literacy")
plt.show()
plt.subplot(2,1,2)
x2=lit.iloc[:,6]
y2=lit.iloc[:,9]
plt.scatter(x2,y2,s=x2*3,alpha=0.3,color="red")
plt.xlabel("2001 literacy")
plt.ylabel("2011 literacy")
plt.show()
sns.pointplot(x="1991 - Male",y="1991 - Female",data=data)
plt.show()
sns.boxplot(x="2001 - Male",y="2001 - Female",data=data)
plt.show()
sns.lmplot(x="2011 - Urban - Male",y="2011 - Urban - Female",data=data)
plt.show()
